# Project-local BYOC OAuth credentials.
#
# 1. Copy this file to `.env` (gitignored).
# 2. Paste in your real client id (and optionally secret).
# 3. Launch:  bun run tauri dev
#
# No `cargo clean` needed — src-tauri/build.rs declares
# `cargo:rerun-if-changed=.env`, so Cargo automatically recompiles
# clients.rs whenever you edit this file.
#
# These are PUBLIC identifiers (not secrets) — we still gitignore the
# real .env so your personal dev credentials don't get committed.

# GitHub OAuth App with Device Flow enabled.
# Register at: https://github.com/settings/applications/new
LATTICE_GITHUB_CLIENT_ID=Iv23li_REPLACE_ME

# Google Cloud OAuth client (Desktop application type).
# Register at: https://console.cloud.google.com/apis/credentials
LATTICE_GOOGLE_CLIENT_ID=REPLACE_ME.apps.googleusercontent.com

# Optional — only set if your Google Cloud project requires a client
# secret for the Desktop client. PKCE alone is usually sufficient.
# LATTICE_GOOGLE_CLIENT_SECRET=GOCSPX-REPLACE_ME
